PicoRAM Wipe On - graphical 3x3 Merlin/Lights-Out style puzzle with sound.
Goal: switch all 9 cells ON. Press 1-9 to apply the given toggle mask. Press 0 for a new puzzle.
One bank; no PicoRAM firmware changes; no nested CALL/RET.

Register allocation:
  R0 top row bits, R1 middle row bits, R2 bottom row bits
  R3 key input / note number, R4 move counter
  R5/R6/R7 row masks for current key
  R8/R9 scratch for drawing and XOR toggle
  RD/RE/RF random start rows and delay counters

Toggle masks, row bit values: left=1, middle=2, right=4
  1: 3,3,0
  2: 7,0,0
  3: 6,6,0
  4: 1,1,1
  5: 2,7,2
  6: 4,4,4
  7: 0,3,3
  8: 0,0,7
  9: 0,6,6

00: CE7  GOTO STARTCLR  INIT:      clear regs+OLED once, then build puzzle
01: F05  RND                       RND -> R_D,R_E,R_F
02: 37D  ANDI 7,D                  R_D &= 7
03: 37E  ANDI 7,E                  R_E &= 7
04: 37F  ANDI 7,F                  R_F &= 7
05: 0D0  MOV D,0                   R0 = R_D top row
06: 0E1  MOV E,1                   R1 = R_E middle row
07: 0F2  MOV F,2                   R2 = R_F bottom row
08: 970  CMPI 7,0                  is top row already 7?
09: E0B  BRZ 0B                    if yes check row 1
0A: C12  GOTO 12                   otherwise draw
0B: 971  CMPI 7,1       ALL7A:     is middle row already 7?
0C: E0E  BRZ 0E                    if yes check row 2
0D: C12  GOTO 12                   otherwise draw
0E: 972  CMPI 7,2       ALL7B:     is bottom row already 7?
0F: E11  BRZ 11                    if all rows are 7, make it unsolved
10: C12  GOTO 12                   otherwise draw
11: 101  MOVI 0,1       FIXALL:    R1 = 0 so starting board is not already solved
12: F14  DISP 1,4       REDRAW:    LED display: move counter R4
13: 909  CMPI 0,9                  (no-op; per-move OLED clear removed -> overwrite)
14: 508  OLED CURSOR               OLED cursor x=4, y=0
15: 055  TX 5 (center MERLIN)
16: 000  lit 0                     TY 0
17: 506  OLED CHAR 'M'
18: 0DD  low D
19: 044  high 4
1A: 506  OLED CHAR 'E'
1B: 055  low 5
1C: 044  high 4
1D: 506  OLED CHAR 'R'
1E: 022  low 2
1F: 055  high 5
20: 506  OLED CHAR 'L'
21: 0CC  low C
22: 044  high 4
23: 506  OLED CHAR 'I'
24: 099  low 9
25: 044  high 4
26: 506  OLED CHAR 'N'
27: 0EE  low E
28: 044  high 4
29: 506  OLED CHAR ' '
2A: 000  low 0
2B: 022  high 2
2C: 508  OLED CURSOR               OLED cursor x=6, y=1
2D: 066  lit 6                     TX 6
2E: 011  lit 1                     TY 1
2F: 008  MOV 0,8                   R8 = top row
30: B9C  CALL 9C                   draw top row
31: 508  OLED CURSOR               OLED cursor x=6, y=2
32: 066  lit 6                     TX 6
33: 022  lit 2                     TY 2
34: 018  MOV 1,8                   R8 = middle row
35: B9C  CALL 9C                   draw middle row
36: 508  OLED CURSOR               OLED cursor x=6, y=3
37: 066  lit 6                     TX 6
38: 033  lit 3                     TY 3
39: 028  MOV 2,8                   R8 = bottom row
3A: B9C  CALL 9C                   draw bottom row
3B: 504  OLED REFRESH              OLED refresh
3C: 50D  PLAY NOTE                 PicoRAM play note stop tone
3D: 000  lit 0                     octave 0
3E: 000  lit 0                     note 0
3F: 970  CMPI 7,0                  top row == 7?
40: E42  BRZ 42                    yes: check middle
41: C48  GOTO 48                   no: wait for key
42: 971  CMPI 7,1       CHK1:      middle row == 7?
43: E45  BRZ 45                    yes: check bottom
44: C48  GOTO 48                   no: wait
45: 972  CMPI 7,2       CHK2:      bottom row == 7?
46: EBB  BRZ BB                    yes: victory melody
47: C48  GOTO 48                   no: wait
48: FF3  KIN 3          WAIT:      wait for key into R3
49: 903  CMPI 0,3       WAITKEY:   key 0 -> cell 7 (bottom-left)
4A: E76  BRZ 76                    KEY7
4B: 913  CMPI 1,3                  key 1 -> cell 8
4C: E7A  BRZ 7A                    KEY8
4D: 923  CMPI 2,3                  key 2 -> cell 9
4E: E7E  BRZ 7E                    KEY9
4F: 943  CMPI 4,3                  key 4 -> cell 4
50: E6A  BRZ 6A                    KEY4
51: 953  CMPI 5,3                  key 5 -> cell 5
52: E6E  BRZ 6E                    KEY5
53: 963  CMPI 6,3                  key 6 -> cell 6
54: E72  BRZ 72                    KEY6
55: 983  CMPI 8,3                  key 8 -> cell 1 (top-left)
56: E5E  BRZ 5E                    KEY1
57: 993  CMPI 9,3                  key 9 -> cell 2
58: E62  BRZ 62                    KEY2
59: 9A3  CMPI A,3                  key A -> cell 3
5A: E66  BRZ 66                    KEY3
5B: 9F3  CMPI F,3                  key F -> new puzzle
5C: E00  BRZ 00
5D: C48  GOTO 48                   ignore other keys
5E: 135  MOVI 3,5       KEY1:      mask top = 3
5F: 136  MOVI 3,6                  mask middle = 3
60: 107  MOVI 0,7                  mask bottom = 0
61: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
62: 175  MOVI 7,5       KEY2:      mask top = 7
63: 106  MOVI 0,6                  mask middle = 0
64: 107  MOVI 0,7                  mask bottom = 0
65: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
66: 165  MOVI 6,5       KEY3:      mask top = 6
67: 166  MOVI 6,6                  mask middle = 6
68: 107  MOVI 0,7                  mask bottom = 0
69: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
6A: 115  MOVI 1,5       KEY4:      mask top = 1
6B: 116  MOVI 1,6                  mask middle = 1
6C: 117  MOVI 1,7                  mask bottom = 1
6D: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
6E: 125  MOVI 2,5       KEY5:      mask top = 2
6F: 176  MOVI 7,6                  mask middle = 7
70: 127  MOVI 2,7                  mask bottom = 2
71: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
72: 145  MOVI 4,5       KEY6:      mask top = 4
73: 146  MOVI 4,6                  mask middle = 4
74: 147  MOVI 4,7                  mask bottom = 4
75: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
76: 105  MOVI 0,5       KEY7:      mask top = 0
77: 136  MOVI 3,6                  mask middle = 3
78: 137  MOVI 3,7                  mask bottom = 3
79: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
7A: 105  MOVI 0,5       KEY8:      mask top = 0
7B: 106  MOVI 0,6                  mask middle = 0
7C: 177  MOVI 7,7                  mask bottom = 7
7D: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
7E: 105  MOVI 0,5       KEY9:      mask top = 0
7F: 166  MOVI 6,6                  mask middle = 6
80: 167  MOVI 6,7                  mask bottom = 6
81: C82  GOTO 82                   apply mask
82: CDB  GOTO APPLY2     APPLY:     crisp key beep, then silent toggle/redraw
83: C85  (dead) GOTO 85
84: C85  (dead) GOTO 85
85: 008  MOV 0,8                   R8 = R0
86: F88  INV 8                     R8 = ~R8
87: 258  AND 5,8                   R8 = R8 & R5
88: 059  MOV 5,9                   R9 = R5
89: F89  INV 9                     R9 = ~R9
8A: 290  AND 9,0                   R0 = R0 & R9
8B: A80  OR 8,0                    R0 = R0 | R8
8C: 018  MOV 1,8                   R8 = R1
8D: F88  INV 8                     R8 = ~R8
8E: 268  AND 6,8                   R8 = R8 & R6
8F: 069  MOV 6,9                   R9 = R6
90: F89  INV 9                     R9 = ~R9
91: 291  AND 9,1                   R1 = R1 & R9
92: A81  OR 8,1                    R1 = R1 | R8
93: 028  MOV 2,8                   R8 = R2
94: F88  INV 8                     R8 = ~R8
95: 278  AND 7,8                   R8 = R8 & R7
96: 079  MOV 7,9                   R9 = R7
97: F89  INV 9                     R9 = ~R9
98: 292  AND 9,2                   R2 = R2 & R9
99: A82  OR 8,2                    R2 = R2 | R8
9A: 514  ADDI 1,4                  move counter++
9B: C12  GOTO 12                   redraw after move
9C: 089  MOV 8,9        DRAWROW:   R9 = R8 for bit 1
9D: 319  ANDI 1,9                  R9 &= 1
9E: EA3  BRZ A3                    if 0 print dot
9F: 506  OLED CHAR                 OLED char 'O'
A0: 0FF  lit F                     arg low F
A1: 044  lit 4                     arg high 4
A2: CA6  GOTO A6                   next cell
A3: 506  OLED CHAR      DROFF1:    OLED char '.'
A4: 0EE  lit E                     arg low E
A5: 022  lit 2                     arg high 2
A6: 089  MOV 8,9        DRCELL2:   R9 = R8 for bit 2
A7: 329  ANDI 2,9                  R9 &= 2
A8: EAD  BRZ AD                    if 0 print dot
A9: 506  OLED CHAR                 OLED char 'O'
AA: 0FF  lit F                     arg low F
AB: 044  lit 4                     arg high 4
AC: CB0  GOTO B0                   next cell
AD: 506  OLED CHAR      DROFF2:    OLED char '.'
AE: 0EE  lit E                     arg low E
AF: 022  lit 2                     arg high 2
B0: 089  MOV 8,9        DRCELL3:   R9 = R8 for bit 4
B1: 349  ANDI 4,9                  R9 &= 4
B2: EB7  BRZ B7                    if 0 print dot
B3: 506  OLED CHAR                 OLED char 'O'
B4: 0FF  lit F                     arg low F
B5: 044  lit 4                     arg high 4
B6: F07  RET                       RET from DRAWROW
B7: 506  OLED CHAR      DROFF3:    OLED char '.'
B8: 0EE  lit E                     arg low E
B9: 022  lit 2                     arg high 2
BA: F07  RET                       RET from DRAWROW
BB: 50D  PLAY NOTE      WIN:       PicoRAM play note win C
BC: 044  lit 4                     octave 4
BD: 011  lit 1                     note 1
BE: BD0  CALL D0                   delay
BF: 50D  PLAY NOTE                 PicoRAM play note win E
C0: 044  lit 4                     octave 4
C1: 055  lit 5                     note 5
C2: BD0  CALL D0                   delay
C3: 50D  PLAY NOTE                 PicoRAM play note win G
C4: 044  lit 4                     octave 4
C5: 088  lit 8                     note 8
C6: BD0  CALL D0                   delay
C7: 50D  PLAY NOTE                 PicoRAM play note win high C
C8: 055  lit 5                     octave 5
C9: 011  lit 1                     note 1
CA: BD0  CALL D0                   delay
CB: 50D  PLAY NOTE                 PicoRAM play note stop tone
CC: 000  lit 0                     octave 0
CD: 000  lit 0                     note 0
CE: FF3  KIN 3                     wait for any key
CF: C00  GOTO 00                   new puzzle
D0: 11E  MOVI 1,E       DELAY:     outer = 1  (melody ~19x faster)
D1: 1CF  MOVI C,F       DLO1:      inner = 12
D2: 71F  SUBI 1,F       DLO2:      R_F--
D3: 90F  CMPI 0,F                  R_F == 0?
D4: ED6  BRZ D6                    inner loop done
D5: CD2  GOTO D2                   inner loop
D6: 71E  SUBI 1,E       DLO1END:   R_E--
D7: 90E  CMPI 0,E                  R_E == 0?
D8: EDA  BRZ DA                    done
D9: CD1  GOTO D1                   outer loop
DA: F07  RET            DRET:      RET from DELAY


APPLY2 - short key beep: play note, brief delay (R_F=5 ~0.4s @ ~50Hz; tunable),
mute, then GOTO the toggle. Played up front so it is independent of the slow redraw.
DB: 50D  PLAY NOTE     APPLY2:    key tone
DC: 044  octave 4
DD: 055  note 5 (fixed; every key incl. 0 beeps)
DE: 15F  MOVI 5,F                 R_F = 5  (short delay)
DF: 71F  SUBI 1,F      A2LOOP:    R_F--
E0: 90F  CMPI 0,F
E1: EE3  BRZ E3
E2: CDF  GOTO DF                  delay loop
E3: 50D  PLAY NOTE     A2MUTE:    mute tone
E4: 000  octave 0
E5: 000  note 0
E6: C85  GOTO 85                  into the toggle (then normal REDRAW)


STARTCLR - clear registers and OLED once per game, then fall into INIT.
E7: F08  CLEAR         STARTCLR:  clear registers
E8: 502  OLED CLEAR               clear screen (once, not every move)
E9: C01  GOTO 01                  continue INIT (RND, build board)

Last used address: E9
CALL/RET audit: REDRAW is reached by GOTO, not CALL. It calls DRAWROW three times, and DRAWROW contains no CALL. WIN is reached by GOTO/BRZ after all row calls have returned; it calls DELAY, and DELAY contains no CALL.
